{# SAR / STR draft package (v0.35.10, roadmap E3).

   DRAFT ONLY — Recupero is not a filer. The obligated financial institution
   (or POCA reporter) completes the institution identifiers + officer
   attestation and submits via the named portal. Every subject / amount / date
   below is derived from the traced case; nothing is fabricated.

   Required Jinja context (build_sar_context):
     case_id, generated_at, incident_date, incident_type, total_loss_usd
     victim{name, jurisdiction}; investigator{name, organization, email}
     labels{report_acronym, report_name, regulator, form_reference, statute,
            filing_portal, characterization}
     subjects[]{address, chain, role, venue, amount_usd}
     activity{amount_usd, date_from, date_to, characterization}
     sar_narrative; tx_evidence[]{tx_hash, block_time, amount_usd, explorer_url}
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>{{ labels.report_acronym }} Draft — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">{{ labels.statute }}</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">{{ labels.regulator }} — {{ labels.form_reference }}</div>
    <h1>{{ labels.report_name }}<br/>Draft Package</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Draft {{ labels.report_acronym }} prepared for review and filing by the
      obligated financial institution pursuant to {{ labels.statute }}.
      Submit via {{ labels.filing_portal }}.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content">

<p style="border:2px solid #b00; padding:10px 14px; border-radius:6px;
          background:#fff5f5; color:#7a0000;">
  <strong>DRAFT — NOT YET FILED.</strong> Recupero LLC is an investigation
  service, not a financial institution, and has no {{ labels.report_acronym }}
  filing obligation or filing credentials. This package compiles the on-chain
  facts to accelerate filing by the obligated institution. The filing
  institution must supply its own identifiers, verify every field, complete the
  officer attestation, and submit via {{ labels.filing_portal }}. Recupero makes
  no representation that a {{ labels.report_acronym }} is required in any
  particular case — that determination rests with the filer.
</p>

<h2>1. Filing Institution</h2>
<p>
[TODO — completed by the filing institution]<br/>
Institution name, registration / EIN, primary federal regulator, filing
contact, and the responsible officer's attestation are supplied by the
obligated institution at the time of filing.
</p>

<h2>2. Subject(s) of the Report</h2>
<p>
The following on-chain addresses received or currently hold the suspected
proceeds. They are identified by wallet address (no natural-person identity is
asserted by Recupero); the filing institution attaches any KYC-resolved
identity it holds for an address under its control.
</p>
{% if subjects %}
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>#</th><th>Address</th><th>Chain</th><th>Role</th><th>Venue</th><th>USD</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for s in subjects %}
    <tr>
      <td>{{ loop.index }}</td>
      <td class="mono">{{ s.address }}</td>
      <td>{{ s.chain }}</td>
      <td>{{ s.role }}</td>
      <td>{{ s.venue }}</td>
      <td>{{ s.amount_usd }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p><em>No identified destination addresses in the trace. The filing
institution should confirm subject identification before filing.</em></p>
{% endif %}

<h2>3. Suspicious Activity</h2>
<table>
  <tbody>
    <tr><th>Aggregate amount (USD-equiv.)</th><td>{{ activity.amount_usd }}</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Activity date range</th><td>{{ activity.date_from or "[date]" }} — {{ activity.date_to or "[date]" }}</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Characterization</th><td>{{ activity.characterization }}</td></tr>
    <tr><th>Underlying incident</th><td>{{ incident_type }}</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>4. Narrative</h2>
<p>{{ sar_narrative }}</p>
<p>
Methodology: the funds flow was reconstructed from public-blockchain data using
deterministic on-chain tracing with chain-of-custody-preserved evidence
receipts. Cross-chain hops, where present, were confirmed by the bridge
protocols' own cross-chain identifiers. Confidence and provenance for each
labeled address are recorded in the underlying case file and are reproducible.
</p>

<h2>5. Supporting Transaction Evidence</h2>
{% if tx_evidence %}
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Tx Hash</th><th>Block Time (UTC)</th><th>USD Amount</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for tx in tx_evidence %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ tx.tx_hash }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.block_time }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.amount_usd }}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>
{% else %}
<p><em>No itemized transaction evidence in the brief; see the full case file.</em></p>
{% endif %}

<h2>6. Filing Instructions</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Review every field; the filing institution is responsible for accuracy.</li>
  <li>Complete Section 1 (filing institution + officer attestation).</li>
  <li>Confirm subject identification against the institution's own KYC records.</li>
  <li>File via {{ labels.filing_portal }} within the statutory deadline.</li>
  <li>Retain this package and the underlying case file as supporting documentation.</li>
</ol>

<p style="margin-top:24px; color:#555;">
Prepared by {{ investigator.organization }} — contact {{ investigator.name }},
{{ investigator.email }}. Case reference: {{ case_id }}.
</p>

</section>
</body>
</html>
